WEBVTT

00:21.847 --> 00:23.458
FELIX:
Hey, Murph.

00:23.501 --> 00:25.373
How about some breakfast?I'm good.

00:27.723 --> 00:28.985
Funeral starts
in a couple hours.

00:29.029 --> 00:30.639
You might want to
eat something.

00:34.686 --> 00:36.471
No, I said I'm good.
I don't want anything.

00:39.474 --> 00:41.606
Come on, you haven't
had any food in days.

00:43.173 --> 00:44.348
[grunts]

00:44.392 --> 00:47.308
Will you just take one
bite for me, please?

00:47.351 --> 00:48.570
I'm not hungry, Felix.

00:52.313 --> 00:53.401
Murph...

00:54.576 --> 00:55.794
[sighs]

00:57.318 --> 00:58.928
It's gonna get easier.

01:02.323 --> 01:04.629
You're going to find
a reason to live again.

01:08.068 --> 01:09.765
I can't imagine
how you must feel,

01:09.808 --> 01:11.419
but I promise you'll
get through this.

01:12.550 --> 01:14.944
And...
[clears throat]

01:14.987 --> 01:18.121
[echoing]: I know it feels like
there's no point of anything.

01:18.165 --> 01:20.167
Of living,
even. But...

01:21.472 --> 01:22.778
...what you've been
going through--

01:22.821 --> 01:25.955
let's just take it
day by day, all right?

01:25.998 --> 01:27.783
♪

01:41.536 --> 01:43.494
[indistinct conversation]

01:43.538 --> 01:45.583
[organ playing in distance]

01:55.637 --> 01:57.639
Hang on. Just
gi-give me a minute.

01:59.684 --> 02:01.338
Oh, my God,
I'm so hot.

02:01.382 --> 02:03.645
Yeah, it's finally
warming up, huh?

02:04.602 --> 02:06.648
[exhales]

02:08.606 --> 02:10.042
You okay?

02:10.086 --> 02:11.827
No, I'm not.

02:14.308 --> 02:17.006
On my way here, I'm just
thinking about how, like...

02:18.442 --> 02:19.791
...nothing changes.

02:19.835 --> 02:22.838
The people are still
getting their coffee,

02:22.881 --> 02:25.667
and texting their dumb friends,
and sitting in traffic and...

02:28.235 --> 02:30.802
The world doesn't even stop
for, like, a second,

02:30.846 --> 02:32.413
like, or one minute
so I can breathe.

02:32.456 --> 02:33.501
JOSH:
Hello, Murphy.

02:38.810 --> 02:40.290
What are you doing here?

02:41.465 --> 02:43.815
Thought I'd come by
and pay my respects.

02:43.859 --> 02:45.817
How you holding up?

02:45.861 --> 02:47.297
DARNELL:
Just walk away, Josh.

02:47.341 --> 02:49.604
FELIX:
Darnell, he's not worth it, man.

02:49.647 --> 02:51.693
I'll see you
in there.

02:56.524 --> 02:58.047
LESLEY:
Don't let him
get to you, Murphy.

02:58.090 --> 02:58.874
Just ignore him.

03:03.618 --> 03:04.880
FELIX:
We should go inside.

03:04.923 --> 03:06.621
DARNELL:
Yeah, let's...

03:08.188 --> 03:09.928
FELIX:
You ready?

03:33.517 --> 03:35.693
[sniffles, clears throat]

03:39.131 --> 03:40.524
Um...

03:42.309 --> 03:44.963
I'm not good
at these things, at-at, uh...

03:45.007 --> 03:47.096
I'm not good at...

03:47.139 --> 03:50.273
talking about my feelings
to, uh, a bunch of people.

03:50.317 --> 03:53.276
I'm not even good at talking
about my feelings to...

03:53.320 --> 03:55.583
like, one person. Um...

03:59.587 --> 04:02.981
That was the thing about Max.

04:05.680 --> 04:07.159
He somehow, like...

04:08.552 --> 04:10.337
...pulled my emotions out of me.

04:10.380 --> 04:13.688
I-I was kicking and screaming,
but he still did it.

04:13.731 --> 04:15.864
And he called me stubborn.

04:15.907 --> 04:17.344
[chuckles softly]

04:23.350 --> 04:25.003
Um, I remember one time...

04:25.047 --> 04:27.310
[sniffles]

04:27.354 --> 04:30.270
...Max was lying next to me
he was, he-he was sleeping.

04:30.313 --> 04:31.314
And...

04:32.315 --> 04:34.535
[chuckles softly]

04:34.578 --> 04:36.014
And-and he laughed.

04:36.058 --> 04:37.799
He-he laughed
while he was sleeping.

04:42.238 --> 04:44.980
I mean, he had every reason
to be self-loathing

04:45.023 --> 04:47.330
and-and feel sorry for himself,

04:47.374 --> 04:48.897
for the hand he was dealt,
but he-he didn't.

04:51.639 --> 04:52.988
He laughed
in his sleep.

04:56.383 --> 04:58.167
[sniffles]

05:06.393 --> 05:07.959
He gave me happiness.

05:11.136 --> 05:13.138
I didn't even think
that was possible, like...

05:14.575 --> 05:15.750
...to actually be happy,

05:15.793 --> 05:17.360
but he-he gave...

05:17.404 --> 05:19.014
he gave me that.

05:22.800 --> 05:24.715
And I will miss him
every single second

05:24.759 --> 05:26.630
of every single day.

05:29.198 --> 05:31.026
For the rest of my life.

05:38.250 --> 05:39.556
[sniffles]

05:39.600 --> 05:41.253
People-people
keep saying to me,

05:41.297 --> 05:44.213
"Oh, uh...

05:44.256 --> 05:45.388
God called him home."

05:45.432 --> 05:46.911
Well...

05:48.826 --> 05:50.437
...God had
nothing to do with this,

05:50.480 --> 05:52.830
and I'm pretty sure
that if God does exist,

05:52.874 --> 05:54.615
he has enough people
to hang out with.

05:54.658 --> 05:58.183
He did not need Max, too.
I needed him.

05:58.227 --> 06:01.839
And the reason Max isn't here...

06:01.883 --> 06:04.320
is because of
another human being.

06:06.104 --> 06:08.672
There is a person out there

06:08.716 --> 06:10.979
that took the love of my life

06:11.022 --> 06:12.807
away from me.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.292
I was just told

06:20.336 --> 06:22.338
that I need to find
a reason for living,

06:22.382 --> 06:23.339
I need to find a purpose.

06:28.126 --> 06:29.389
Well, I found one.

06:30.520 --> 06:32.435
I have one.

06:32.479 --> 06:35.699
I am going to find
the person that did this.

06:35.743 --> 06:38.659
And I am going to make them pay

06:38.702 --> 06:40.617
for what they've done!

07:01.116 --> 07:03.901
You know, I feel like I have
to say for the record,

07:03.945 --> 07:05.860
um, that's not
really what I meant.

07:05.903 --> 07:08.602
No, I know,
but I have to do this.

07:08.645 --> 07:09.994
Okay, so...

07:10.038 --> 07:11.256
what's your big plan--

07:11.300 --> 07:12.519
you gonna break
into prison

07:12.562 --> 07:13.650
and cut off Jimmy
McKay's ding-dong or...

07:13.694 --> 07:15.217
No, I don't care about Jimmy.

07:15.260 --> 07:16.348
He's gonna rot in prison.

07:18.829 --> 07:20.657
I'm after whoever
tipped him off.

07:21.832 --> 07:23.138
Whoever called him, that...

07:24.792 --> 07:26.794
Whoever wanted everything
to get messed up--

07:26.837 --> 07:29.405
that's the person that is
responsible for Max's death.

07:29.449 --> 07:31.233
Jimmy's just the one
who pulled the trigger.

07:32.190 --> 07:33.453
Murphy?

07:36.760 --> 07:38.370
Hey, Chloe.

07:38.414 --> 07:39.763
Hey, Chlo.

07:39.807 --> 07:41.417
I'll give you
two a minute.

07:46.335 --> 07:47.684
You came.

07:49.120 --> 07:50.382
[sighs]

07:50.426 --> 07:53.516
I heard what happened about Max.

07:55.039 --> 07:57.781
And I don't know
all the details,

07:57.825 --> 07:59.957
but...

08:00.001 --> 08:01.568
I know it had something to do

08:01.611 --> 08:04.527
with that stupid pill I took.

08:04.571 --> 08:06.486
No, Chloe. No.

08:07.835 --> 08:09.445
It has nothing
to do with you.

08:09.489 --> 08:12.230
I don't want you
feeling guilty for one second.

08:13.797 --> 08:15.756
Okay.

08:15.799 --> 08:17.758
Well...

08:17.801 --> 08:20.543
I still wanted to come
and say I'm sorry.

08:20.587 --> 08:22.240
[sniffles]

08:22.284 --> 08:23.807
I'm really happy you're here.

08:27.594 --> 08:28.769
[chuckles]

08:28.812 --> 08:31.467
It's nice to see her
smile, though.

08:31.511 --> 08:33.730
Okay, but you did
tell her she can't do

08:33.774 --> 08:35.558
whatever it is she's
planning on doing, right?

08:35.602 --> 08:37.168
No, I'm just...
[clears throat]

08:37.212 --> 08:38.735
gonna give her
a little bit of time.Felix.

08:38.779 --> 08:40.998
What? She...
This is how she copes.

08:41.042 --> 08:43.392
She needs to focus on something.
I don't know.

08:43.435 --> 08:44.959
I mean, at least
she's off the couch, right?

08:46.221 --> 08:47.614
Whatever.
Let's just hope

08:47.657 --> 08:49.833
she doesn't find
whoever this person is.

08:49.877 --> 08:52.096
How would
she do that?

08:52.140 --> 08:54.098
[door buzzes][lock clicks]

08:54.142 --> 08:56.579
You know, when I saw your name
on the visitor's log,

08:56.623 --> 08:58.973
I have to admit I was surprised.

09:00.322 --> 09:02.846
Yeah, well, I just came to ask
who called you that night.

09:02.890 --> 09:05.893
[exhales] I'm sorry?Someone called you

09:05.936 --> 09:08.286
to tell you we were
setting you up. Who was it?

09:10.375 --> 09:12.029
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

09:17.121 --> 09:20.777
You know, the prosecution is
going to call me as a witness.

09:20.821 --> 09:22.518
I know you're claiming
self-defense,

09:22.562 --> 09:23.998
that Max attacked you.

09:25.347 --> 09:28.872
And I was planning on
telling the truth, but...

09:28.916 --> 09:31.179
...I'm willing to go along
with your little story.

09:33.224 --> 09:35.662
All you have to do is tell me
who called you that night.

09:38.752 --> 09:40.057
And if you don't...

09:41.406 --> 09:43.104
...I'll bury you.

09:45.454 --> 09:47.282
[laughs]

09:49.676 --> 09:52.374
Oh, relax. Just relax.

09:54.681 --> 09:57.597
He said he was with Chicago PD.

09:57.640 --> 09:59.773
He had a British accent.

10:01.949 --> 10:03.777
Was his name Josh Wallace?

10:05.430 --> 10:07.911
Yeah. Yeah, that was it.

10:13.003 --> 10:16.616
Josh?Yep. I know.

10:16.659 --> 10:18.008
Oh, my God.

10:21.185 --> 10:22.230
Oh, my God.

10:22.273 --> 10:25.233
I want to kill Josh.
Serious.

10:25.276 --> 10:26.756
You're not gonna kill anyone.Yeah, I am.

10:26.800 --> 10:27.975
Murph, you're not just
gonna kill someone.

10:28.018 --> 10:29.150
Yeah, I am.
It's not just someone.

10:29.193 --> 10:31.152
It's Josh.

10:31.195 --> 10:33.241
And he loved that this happened.
He went to the funeral to gloat.

10:33.284 --> 10:35.373
He's-he's a psychopath.

10:37.071 --> 10:39.203
He's psychotic.

10:39.247 --> 10:40.727
Murph.

10:40.770 --> 10:42.206
I'm just asking you to
take a beat, please.

10:42.250 --> 10:44.861
I'm taking a beat.
What do you think this is?

10:44.905 --> 10:46.254
This is beat to figure out

10:46.297 --> 10:47.777
how to kill Josh
without getting caught.

10:47.821 --> 10:49.387
Oh, my God.That's my beat.

10:49.431 --> 10:50.650
Okay, look.

10:50.693 --> 10:51.912
I know we've done some...

10:51.955 --> 10:53.696
very bad things.

10:53.740 --> 10:55.306
Okay? In our lives,

10:55.350 --> 10:58.440
And I know you've-you've
seen more death than,

10:58.483 --> 11:01.617
you know, the
average joe.

11:01.661 --> 11:03.053
But you've never...

11:03.097 --> 11:04.011
you've never actually
killed anyone.

11:07.667 --> 11:08.493
Murphy...

11:09.669 --> 11:13.063
Max loved you, okay?

11:13.107 --> 11:16.066
He loved you so much.

11:16.110 --> 11:19.504
And he would not want you
to spend the rest of your life

11:19.548 --> 11:21.332
behind bars
on his account.

11:22.594 --> 11:24.988
He would want you
to live your life.

11:26.555 --> 11:28.122
That's what
he would want.

11:30.080 --> 11:31.081
So, please.

11:32.126 --> 11:35.477
Just... drop this.

11:35.520 --> 11:37.131
For his sake.

11:43.093 --> 11:44.529
Yeah.

11:47.358 --> 11:48.533
[sniffles]

11:49.839 --> 11:51.711
You're right. I'm just...

11:51.754 --> 11:53.060
I'm just being stupid.

11:53.103 --> 11:54.539
[sniffles]It's okay.

11:56.324 --> 11:57.673
I love you.

12:12.340 --> 12:14.603
[sniffles]

12:25.005 --> 12:26.833
♪

12:47.767 --> 12:49.769
♪

13:14.968 --> 13:17.013
♪

13:32.594 --> 13:35.075
Pretzel, come on.[snaps fingers]

13:35.118 --> 13:36.467
Let's go.

13:58.272 --> 14:00.056
[glass breaking in distance]

14:25.038 --> 14:26.300
[whispering]: Stay.

14:27.257 --> 14:28.302
Stay.

14:33.220 --> 14:35.352
[door creaking]

14:35.396 --> 14:37.441
[panting]

14:55.895 --> 14:56.808
[panting]

15:08.559 --> 15:09.647
Josh.

15:10.692 --> 15:11.867
Josh!

15:13.129 --> 15:14.130
Josh!

15:15.131 --> 15:16.785
Josh!

15:18.221 --> 15:20.267
[crying]

15:35.891 --> 15:37.675
[Pretzel panting][door opens]

15:48.251 --> 15:50.645
[door closes][keys jingling]

15:50.688 --> 15:51.863
Pretzel, get out. Go, go.

16:03.266 --> 16:04.789
FELIX:
Is-is anyone in there?

16:07.879 --> 16:09.316
Hello?

16:09.359 --> 16:10.795
What the hell
are you doing in here?Aah!

16:10.839 --> 16:12.580
What the hell are
you doing here?

16:12.623 --> 16:14.625
You followed me?I woke up and I saw
you weren't there.

16:14.669 --> 16:15.887
What... I don't...

16:15.931 --> 16:16.714
Please tell me
you didn't...

16:16.758 --> 16:19.152
Oh, my God. No!

16:19.195 --> 16:21.981
He's not even home.Thank God.

16:23.330 --> 16:24.722
What the hell, Murphy?

16:24.766 --> 16:26.072
I thought you said
you were good.

16:26.115 --> 16:27.464
I am good.Really?

16:27.508 --> 16:28.726
I am. I-I...

16:28.770 --> 16:30.163
I didn't come here...

16:30.206 --> 16:31.294
I swear. I didn't
come here to do anything.

16:31.338 --> 16:33.122
Oh, okay.

16:33.166 --> 16:34.515
So you just broke into
his house for a cup of tea?

16:34.558 --> 16:37.257
I just needed to talk to him.Talk to him.

16:37.300 --> 16:39.085
Yes.

16:39.128 --> 16:41.043
Okay? I listened
to everything you said.

16:41.087 --> 16:44.786
And I...
I really think I need...

16:44.829 --> 16:47.310
I need to confront Josh,
I need closure.

16:47.354 --> 16:49.356
That's how I'm gonna move on.

16:49.399 --> 16:51.053
And I was afraid
you wouldn't believe me,

16:51.097 --> 16:52.533
so I took the bus.

16:53.490 --> 16:55.362
Closure?Yes.

16:55.405 --> 16:56.624
Closure.

16:57.886 --> 17:00.062
But he's not even here,
so I'm just gonna wait for him.

17:00.106 --> 17:01.368
You can go.

17:04.153 --> 17:06.112
Well, you know,
it is 4:00 in the morning.

17:06.155 --> 17:07.722
Did you think maybe he's not
coming home tonight?

17:09.028 --> 17:11.073
Where would he be?I don't know.

17:11.117 --> 17:12.814
His dog isn't here.

17:12.857 --> 17:14.207
All of his clothes are gone.

17:15.425 --> 17:16.948
He left town.Well,

17:16.992 --> 17:17.949
after what you said
at Max's funeral,

17:17.993 --> 17:19.038
I don't blame him.

17:19.081 --> 17:20.691
Coward.

17:20.735 --> 17:22.737
[sighs]

17:22.780 --> 17:24.043
well, what if he...

17:24.086 --> 17:26.567
He could have gone
back to London.

17:27.742 --> 17:29.352
What if he went...
what if he went home?

17:29.396 --> 17:31.050
What if he...
He could be gone for years.

17:31.093 --> 17:32.747
What if he doesn't come back?

17:32.790 --> 17:34.096
What if he never
comes back here?Okay, okay.

17:34.140 --> 17:35.576
What if I don't get to see him

17:35.619 --> 17:37.143
and talk to him?Okay.

17:37.186 --> 17:38.448
What if I never see him?Shh. Take a breath.

17:40.885 --> 17:42.191
[sighs]

17:44.628 --> 17:48.371
Maybe we can both find out
where he went together.

17:48.415 --> 17:49.851
Okay?

17:55.422 --> 17:56.988
Any clue what
his password is?

17:58.599 --> 17:59.991
No.

18:00.035 --> 18:01.819
Great.

18:01.863 --> 18:04.387
Okay, well, then...

18:04.431 --> 18:07.216
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hang on a second.

18:07.260 --> 18:09.784
Looks like he printed this
out before he left.

18:09.827 --> 18:11.133
What is it?

18:11.177 --> 18:13.875
Okay, here we go.

18:13.918 --> 18:16.051
Vacation rental house
in Branson, Missouri.

18:16.095 --> 18:18.097
We can go to this address
and see if he's there.

18:19.185 --> 18:20.621
You don't have to
drive me, though.

18:20.664 --> 18:22.013
Yeah, I'll just
let you hitchhike.

18:22.057 --> 18:23.276
Of course I'm
gonna drive you.

18:23.319 --> 18:25.495
I'm gonna be with you every step
of every way

18:25.539 --> 18:27.410
in full support,

18:27.454 --> 18:29.238
'cause I think this could
actually be a good idea.

18:29.282 --> 18:31.893
Mm-hmm.Talking to Josh.

18:33.068 --> 18:34.243
Talking to Josh.

18:36.680 --> 18:38.291
Okay.

18:40.336 --> 18:44.079
♪ Why do you keep
torturing me? ♪

18:44.123 --> 18:45.689
♪ Let me know you love me

18:45.733 --> 18:48.431
♪ Or set me free

18:48.475 --> 18:49.824
♪ Let me know

18:49.867 --> 18:52.435
♪ Just how you feel...

18:52.479 --> 18:53.828
Are we there yet?

18:53.871 --> 18:55.786
[nasal voice]: Are we
there yet? Are we there yet?

18:55.830 --> 18:57.005
[normal voice]:
Like a five-year-old.

18:57.048 --> 18:59.181
Well, are we?No, we are not there yet.

18:59.225 --> 19:01.140
If we were there, the car
would not be moving.

19:01.183 --> 19:02.184
Five minutes.

19:02.228 --> 19:04.491
♪ Your love is true

19:04.534 --> 19:05.666
♪ Like the love

19:05.709 --> 19:08.756
♪ I have for you

19:08.799 --> 19:11.150
♪ Yeah, let me know
if your love is... ♪

19:11.193 --> 19:12.803
This is the road.

19:12.847 --> 19:15.415
♪ You know that love can be...

19:15.458 --> 19:17.808
Max would be proud
of you, you know?

19:19.506 --> 19:20.594
Yeah.

19:22.204 --> 19:24.511
I'm sorry, I...[exhales] It's okay.

19:24.554 --> 19:25.903
♪ All ni...

19:35.174 --> 19:36.392
[exhales]

19:38.089 --> 19:41.615
Text Erika dog sitter.
"Just arrived.

19:41.658 --> 19:42.920
How's Oliver doing?"

19:42.964 --> 19:44.618
[phone beeps]

19:44.661 --> 19:47.360
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Cellular service not available.

19:48.361 --> 19:50.014
[sighs] Great.

20:14.604 --> 20:16.040
[engine stops]

20:17.520 --> 20:20.088
FELIX:
[sighs] We're here.

20:20.131 --> 20:23.874
Okay, wait, I think
I should go in alone.

20:23.918 --> 20:25.398
What?

20:25.441 --> 20:27.269
Yeah, I appreciate you...

20:27.313 --> 20:29.358
you know, wanting
to be here for me,

20:29.402 --> 20:32.013
but I-I don't need,
like, a guy

20:32.056 --> 20:33.667
to support me, so....

20:33.710 --> 20:35.799
I-I got-I got it.

20:35.843 --> 20:37.366
Okay.Okay.

20:37.410 --> 20:39.760
I'll be here.All right.

20:39.803 --> 20:42.806
Where's the...
Which way is the house?

20:42.850 --> 20:45.331
It's just, uh, about
30 feet to your left.

20:45.374 --> 20:46.419
Okay.

20:48.334 --> 20:49.552
Thank you.

20:50.597 --> 20:52.773
Why are you bringing
your backpack?

20:54.427 --> 20:55.776
I always take
my backpack with me.

20:55.819 --> 20:57.778
